From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Subject: kABI workaround for HCI_LE_ADV_0 addition
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: git-fixes

The backport for the bt fix commit 0d92808024b4 added a new enum
member HCI_LE_ADV, which shifts all the rest enum values.
To remain them backward compatbile, move the new enum member at the
bottom.
 
The total number should still fit in the same bitmap long array;
now __HCI_NUM_FLAGS becoming 56, so this is the last bit that can be
added, though.

Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 include/net/bluetooth/hci.h |    6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/include/net/bluetooth/hci.h
+++ b/include/net/bluetooth/hci.h
@@ -432,7 +432,6 @@ enum {
 	HCI_USER_CHANNEL,
 	HCI_EXT_CONFIGURED,
 	HCI_LE_ADV,
-	HCI_LE_ADV_0,
 	HCI_LE_PER_ADV,
 	HCI_LE_SCAN,
 	HCI_SSP_ENABLED,
@@ -475,6 +474,11 @@ enum {
 	HCI_MESH,
 	HCI_MESH_SENDING,
 
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
+	/* FIXME: moved here for kABI compatibility */
+	HCI_LE_ADV_0,
+#endif
+
 	__HCI_NUM_FLAGS,
 };
 
